===Etymology===
From {{OF.}} ''[[sucre]]'' ("sugar") < {{ML.}} ''[[succarum]]'' < {{Arab.}} {{ARchar|[[سكر|سُكّر]]}} (súkkar) < {{Pers.}} {{FAchar|[[شکر]]}} (shekar) < {{Skr.}} [[शर्करा]] (sharkara) "ground or candied sugar," originally "grit," "gravel" (cognate with Greek ''[[κρόκη]] "pebble").

